	Sarahs voice    
	 New York, Oct. 23 (PTI): Sex and the City star Sarah Jessica Parker has joined hands with actress Gabourey Sidibe to raise awareness about sex trafficking.      
	The Hollywood A-listers lent their voices to public service announcements drawing attention to a new hotline for trafficking victims, reports the New York Post.      
	At least 100,000 American children are trafficked into prostitution in the United States each year, Parker said in a radio message.      
	Its important that we fight this plague that affects the lives of so many of our children, added the 45-year-old mother-of-three.    
	Ricci body    
	London (PTI): Actress Christina Ricci, who shot to fame at the age of 10 starring in Mermaids with Cher and Winona Ryder, suffered from low self-esteem because of body issues she suffered as a young actress. The Penelope star, who battled anorexia, couldnt stand seeing herself in a mirror as she hated her looks and figure.     
	Robot film    
	 Los Angeles (PTI): Hollywood veteran Steven Spielberg is taking on robots in his next directorial venture. The Jurassic Park director will direct the adaptation of Robopocalypse. The post-apocalyptic story is based on Daniel H Wilson novel. Spielberg is directing the film for DreamWorks and Disney, the Hollywood Reporter said.     
	Elton song    
	 Los Angeles (PTI): Pop stars Lady Gaga and Sir Elton John will collaborate on a new track which will appear in an upcoming Disney movie. The song, called Hello, Hello, will be featured in the animated film Gnomeo amp; Juliet, which is being produced by Johns partner David Furnish, reports Entertainment Weekly. The song will accompany a scene in the movie where the two lead characters meet. John became close friends with Gaga after their performance at the Grammys.                                                                                                                                                       
